	<node custom_icon_id="0" foreground="" is_bold="True" name="Domains" prog_lang="custom-colors" readonly="False" tags="" unique_id="38">
		<rich_text>A cleric can cast any prayer he knows.  Prayers are divided into 3 Tiers per Domain. At each level a cleric can have a certain number of Domains. The first time a character chooses a Domain he gets access to the Tier 1 prayers.  The second time the Domain is chosen he gets the Tier 2 prayers.  The third time he gets Tier 3.  A cleric cannot choose a Domain twice in a row. He must choose another Domain between.

Example: At first level Bob the Righteous gets 1 Domain. He chooses the Good Domain. He now has access to the Tier 1 Good Prayers. At 5th Level Bob gets another Domain. He cannot choose Good because that is what he chose last time.  This time Bob chooses Protection. He now has access to the Tier 1 prayers for the Good and Protection Domains.  At 8th level Bob can again choose the Good Domain or any other Domain except the Protection Domain. He chooses the Good Domain. He can now access the Tier 1 and 2 Prayers of the Good Domain and the Tier 1 Prayers of the Protection Domain.

Tier 1 Powers may be used once per Encounter. They recharge at the end of an Encounter and are immediately usable again.

Tier 2 Powers may be used once and then are recharged at a Short Rest or Long Rest.

Tier 3 Powers may be used once and then are only recharged at a Long Rest.
</rich_text>
		<node custom_icon_id="0" foreground="" is_bold="False" name="Healing Domain" prog_lang="custom-colors" readonly="False" tags="" unique_id="39">
			<rich_text underline="single" weight="heavy">Tier 1</rich_text>
			<rich_text>

Heal Wounds: The cleric can heal an ally with a simple touch. The target gets 1d8 hit points instantly healed, +1 per level of the cleric.

Minor Restoration: Dispels any magical effects reducing one of the subject’s ability scores or cures 1d4 points of temporary ability damage to one of the subject’s ability scores. It does not restore permanent ability drain or level drain.

</rich_text>
			<rich_text underline="single" weight="heavy">Tier 2</rich_text>
			<rich_text>

Healing Aura: The cleric heals all allies within 20 feet. The targets get 1d6 hit points for every 2 levels of the cleric.

Restoration</rich_text>
			<rich_text weight="heavy">:</rich_text>
			<rich_text> Functions like minor restoration, except that it also dispels negative levels and restores one experience level to a creature who has had a level drained. The drained level is restored only if the time since the creature lost the level is equal to or less than one day per caster level. A character who has a level restored by restoration has exactly the minimum number of experience points necessary to restore him or her to his or her previous level.

Restoration cures all temporary ability damage, and it restores all points permanently drained from a single ability score (your choice if more than one is drained). 

Restoration does not restore levels or Constitution points lost due to death.

</rich_text>
			<rich_text underline="single" weight="heavy">Tier 3</rich_text>
			<rich_text>

Heal: Instantly heals all hit point damage, ability damage and level drain suffered by the target. The cleric must touch the intended target.</rich_text>
		</node>
		<node custom_icon_id="0" foreground="" is_bold="False" name="Protection Domain" prog_lang="custom-colors" readonly="False" tags="" unique_id="50">
			<rich_text underline="single" weight="heavy">Tier 1</rich_text>
			<rich_text>

Sanctuary: The cleric makes a Charisma attack vs Willpower against any foe that wants to attack him. If the attack is successful then the foe cannot attack for the duration of the prayer. If the attack is not successful then the foe can attack normally. The cleric attacking an enemy instantly negates the effects of the prayer on that enemy. The prayer lasts for 2d4 rounds. 

Shield Other: This prayer wards the subject and creates a mystic connection between you and the subject so that some of its wounds are transferred to you. The subject gains a +1 to all defences. Additionally, the subject takes only half damage from all wounds and attacks that deal hit point damage. The amount of damage not taken by the warded creature is taken by you. This prayer lasts 2d4 rounds.

</rich_text>
			<rich_text underline="single" weight="heavy">Tier 2</rich_text>
			<rich_text>

Absorb Energy: You absorb 10 points per cleric level of damage from a specific type of energy (fire, cold, negative energy, etc). The type of energy is determined at the time of the prayer. The effect last until all the points are absorbed or the end of the encounter.

Resistance</rich_text>
			<rich_text weight="heavy">:</rich_text>
			<rich_text> Cleric or the target touched gets a +4 bonus to all defences against spells and magical attacks. This lasts until the end of the encounter.

</rich_text>
			<rich_text underline="single" weight="heavy">Tier 3</rich_text>
			<rich_text>

Anti Magic Field: Negates all magic within 10 feet of the cleric (including benefitial magic). Effect lasts for 1 round per level of the cleric.</rich_text>
		</node>
		<node custom_icon_id="0" foreground="" is_bold="False" name="Air Domain" prog_lang="custom-colors" readonly="False" tags="" unique_id="51">
			<rich_text underline="single" weight="heavy">Tier 1</rich_text>
			<rich_text>

Obscuring Mist: A misty vapor arises around you. It is stationary once created. The vapor obscures all sight, including darkvision, beyond 5 feet. The mist lasts for 1 minute per level of the cleric.

Wind Wall: A vertical wall of wind 10 feet long and 5 feet high per cleric level springs up. It is 2 feet thick and of considerable strength. Small flying creatures cannot fly through it. Arrows and crossbow bolts automatically miss if fired through it. Larger projectiles suffer a -4 chance to hit. Giant sized projectiles and seige engines are unaffected. The effect lasts until the end of the encounter. 

</rich_text>
			<rich_text underline="single" weight="heavy">Tier 2</rich_text>
			<rich_text>

Gaseous Form: The cleric or a touched subject and all its gear become insubstantial, misty, and translucent. A gaseous creature can’t run, but it can fly at a speed of 10 feet. It can pass through small holes or narrow openings, even mere cracks, with all it was wearing or holding in its hands, as long as the spell persists. The creature is subject to the effects of wind, and it can’t enter water or other liquid. It also can’t manipulate objects or activate items, even those carried along with its gaseous form. Continuously active items remain active, though in some cases their effects may be moot. The effects last for 2 minutes per cleric level.

Air Walk</rich_text>
			<rich_text weight="heavy">:</rich_text>
			<rich_text> The cleric or a touched target can tread on air as if walking on solid ground. Moving upward is similar to walking up a hill. The maximum upward or downward angle possible is 45 degrees, at a rate equal to one-half the air walker’s normal speed. The effect lasts for 10 minutes per cleric level.

</rich_text>
			<rich_text underline="single" weight="heavy">Tier 3</rich_text>
			<rich_text>

Whirlwind: This prayer creates a powerful cyclone of raging wind that moves through the air, along the ground, or over water at a speed of 60 feet per round. You can concentrate on controlling the cyclone’s every movement or give it simple instructions. Directing the cyclone’s movement or changing its instructions counts as your action for the round and occurs in the Missile / Movement phase. The cyclone always moves during your turn on the Movement phase. If the cyclone gets more than 500 feet from you, it moves in a random, uncontrolled fashion for 1d3 rounds and then dissipates. You can’t regain control of the cyclone, even if comes back within range.

Any Large or smaller creature that comes in contact with the spell effect is attacked at your Base Attack Bonus versus Reflex. A successful attack does 3d6 points of damage. A Medium or smaller creature that takes this damage is attacked again. A success on this attack means the creature is picked up bodily by the cyclone and held suspended in its powerful winds, taking 1d8 points of damage each round on your turn with no save allowed. You may direct the cyclone to eject any carried creatures whenever you wish, depositing the hapless souls wherever the cyclone happens to be when they are released.

This prayer lasts for 1 round per cleric level.</rich_text>
		</node>
		<node custom_icon_id="0" foreground="" is_bold="False" name="Plant Domain" prog_lang="custom-colors" readonly="False" tags="" unique_id="52">
			<rich_text underline="single" weight="heavy">Tier 1</rich_text>
			<rich_text>

Entangle: Grasses, weeds, bushes, and even trees wrap, twist, and entwine about creatures in a 20 foot radius area within 100 feet of the cleric, holding them fast and causing them to become entangled. Caster makes an attack mofified by Wis against each creature in the area's Reflex defence. A successful attack means the target is immobilized. An immobilized target can use it's turn to attempt to break free with a Strength or Escape Artist check against DC 15. Each round that any creature is in the area the cleric makes an attack roll to immobilize them. The effect last for 1d4 +1 round per level of the cleric.

Barkskin: The cleric can touch a target and cause its skin to become hard and bark-like. The target gets a +2 bonus to AC that lasts for 10 minutes per level of the cleric. The bonus gets an additional +1 for every 5 cleric levels.

</rich_text>
			<rich_text underline="single" weight="heavy">Tier 2</rich_text>
			<rich_text>

Wall of Thorns: The cleric can create a wall of thorns that blocks movement. The wall is 10 feet long per cleric level and 5 feet wide. Anyone caught in the wall when it is cast or attempts to move through the wall takes damage: 1d10 for no armor, 1d8 for light armor and 1d6 for medium.  Those in heavy armor or its equivalent are unaffected. Someone can push through the 5 foot width of the wall with a successful Strength check vs a DC of 15. The wall lasts for 10 minutes per cleric level.

Animate Plants</rich_text>
			<rich_text weight="heavy">:</rich_text>
			<rich_text> You imbue inanimate plants with mobility and a semblance of life. Each animated plant then immediately attacks whomever or whatever you initially designate. You may animate one Large or smaller plant per three cleric levels. You can change the designated target in the Move phase of combat. The prayer lasts for 1 round per cleric level. 

TODO: Stats for the Animated Plant.

</rich_text>
			<rich_text underline="single" weight="heavy">Tier 3</rich_text>
			<rich_text>

Shambler: This prayer creates 1d4+2 large Shambling Mounds. The creatures willingly aid you in combat or battle, perform a specific mission, or serve as bodyguards. The creatures remain with you for seven days unless you dismiss them. If the shamblers are created only for guard duty, however, the duration of the spell is seven months. In this case, the shamblers can only be ordered to guard a specific site or location. Shamblers summoned to guard duty cannot move outside the spell’s range, which is measured from the point where each first appeared.

TODO: Stats for the Shambling Mound.</rich_text>
