		<node custom_icon_id="0" foreground="" is_bold="False" name="Animal Domain" prog_lang="custom-colors" readonly="False" tags="" unique_id="53">
			<rich_text underline="single" weight="heavy">Tier 1</rich_text>
			<rich_text>

Calm Animals: Cleric can cause all animals within 30 feet to become docile and harmless. Only ordinary animals can be affected by the spell. If the animal is trained to attack or guard then the cleric must succeed at an base attack plus his Charisma vs the animal's Will defence. The effect lasts for 1 minute per cleric level.

Dominate Animal: You can enchant an animal and direct it with simple commands such as “Attack,” “Run,” and “Fetch.” Suicidal or self-destructive commands (including an order to attack a creature much larger than the dominated animal) are simply ignored. The animal must be within 25 feet of the cleric and the cleric must make a Charisma attack vs the animal's Will defence. The effect lasts 1 round per cleric level.

</rich_text>
			<rich_text underline="single" weight="heavy">Tier 2</rich_text>
			<rich_text>

Summon Nature's Ally: The cleric can summon a natural animal. The animal appears within 25 feet of the cleric. It attacks the clerics opponents to the best of its ability. The cleric must be able to communicate with the animal in order to direct it to attack specific foes or to do other specific actions. The cleric cannot summon an animal with more hit dice than his cleric level. The animal stays for 1 round per cleric level and then disappears.

Commune with Nature</rich_text>
			<rich_text weight="heavy">:</rich_text>
			<rich_text> The cleric instantly gains knowledge of as many as three facts from among the following subjects: the ground or terrain, plants, minerals, bodies of water, people, general animal population, presence of woodland creatures, presence of powerful unnatural creatures, or even the general state of the natural setting. In outdoor settings, the effect spans a radius of 1 mile per caster level. In natural underground settings—caves, caverns, and the like—the radius is limited to 100 feet per caster level. The prayer does not function where nature has been replaced by construction or settlement, such as in dungeons and towns.

</rich_text>
			<rich_text underline="single" weight="heavy">Tier 3</rich_text>
			<rich_text>

Shapechange: The cleric can assume the shape of any animal with equal or fewer hit dice than his cleric levels. The cleric gains all the animal's attacks and special abilities but loses his own special abilities. Items worn and carried are absorbed into the new form and reappear when the effect ends. The cleric can change form once per round on his turn. The effect lasts 10 minutes per level.</rich_text>
		</node>
		<node custom_icon_id="0" foreground="" is_bold="False" name="Sun Domain" prog_lang="custom-colors" readonly="False" tags="" unique_id="54">
			<rich_text underline="single" weight="heavy">Tier 1</rich_text>
			<rich_text>

Heat Metal: Cleric causes metal on targeted creatures within 25 feet to get hot and potentially cause damage.  The cleric can target 1 creature for every 2 cleric levels.  Damage is caused according to the chart below.  If the metal on the creature isn't worn or is very small then it takes minimum damage.

Round   Temp    Damage
----------------------
1       Warm    None
2       Hot     1d4
3-5     Searing 2d4
6       Hot     1d4
7       Warm    None

Searing Light: A successful Wisdom based attack against a target creature within 100 ft causes them to be struck by a focused ray of sunlight from your hand. The target takes 1d8 damage per 2 cleric levels (max 5d8). Undead take 1d6 per caster level (max 10d6). Constructs or inanimate objects take 1d6 per 2 caster levels (max 5d6). 

</rich_text>
			<rich_text underline="single" weight="heavy">Tier 2</rich_text>
			<rich_text>

Fire Shield: The cleric is wreathed in a shield of flames. He takes half damage from cold based attacks.  Any creature that successfully attacks the cleric with a melee attack takes 1d6 +1 per cleric level in fire damage.

Sunbeam</rich_text>
			<rich_text weight="heavy">:</rich_text>
			<rich_text> Once per round the cleric can evoke a dazzling beam of intese light. The cleric gets 1 beam for every 3 cleric levels.  The beams require a Wisdom based attack against a target's Reflex defense.  A successful attack blinds the creature for 1d6 rounds and does 4d6 damage. An unsuccessful attack negates the blindness and delivers only half damage. Undead take double damage.

</rich_text>
			<rich_text underline="single" weight="heavy">Tier 3</rich_text>
			<rich_text>

Sunburst: Cleric causes a 80 foot radius burst of searing radiance at a point within 400 feet. All creatures within the radius are subject to a Wisdom attack versus Reflex. A successful attack blinds the target for 1d6 rounds and does 6d6 damage. A failed attack negates the blindness and does half damage.  Undead take 1d6 damage per cleric level.
</rich_text>
		</node>
		<node custom_icon_id="0" foreground="" is_bold="False" name="War Domain" prog_lang="custom-colors" readonly="False" tags="" unique_id="55">
			<rich_text underline="single" weight="heavy">Tier 1</rich_text>
			<rich_text>

Magic Weapon: Touched weapon gains +1 magic bonus to hit. Bonus lasts for 1 minute per cleric level.

Magic Vestment: Touched armor or shield gains +1 magic bonus per 5 cleric levels (max +3). Bonus lasts 1 hour per cleric level.

</rich_text>
			<rich_text underline="single" weight="heavy">Tier 2</rich_text>
			<rich_text>

Divine Power: The cleric's diety imbues him with strength and skill. The cleric gets the attack bonus and number of attacks of a fighter at the same level. He also gets a +1 to strength per 5 cleric levels (max +3). The effects last for 1 round per 2 cleric levels.

Blade Barrier</rich_text>
			<rich_text weight="heavy">:</rich_text>
			<rich_text> An immobile, vertical curtain of whirling blades shaped of pure force springs into existence. Any creature passing through the wall is subject to a Wisdom based attack versus Reflex.  A successful attack deals 1d6 points of damage per caster level (max 15d6).  A failed attack does half damage.

</rich_text>
			<rich_text underline="single" weight="heavy">Tier 3</rich_text>
			<rich_text>

Power Word Kill: Cleric utters a word and instantly kills a single creature of 100 hit points or less. Creatures with more than 100 hit points are unaffected. Creatures that are already dead are unaffected.
</rich_text>
		</node>
		<node custom_icon_id="0" foreground="" is_bold="False" name="Good Domain" prog_lang="custom-colors" readonly="False" tags="" unique_id="56">
			<rich_text>The Good Domain Prayers often target “evil” foes. What is evil is left up to the GM to judge. However, evil shouldn't be defined as just anyone who opposes the PC.

</rich_text>
			<rich_text underline="single" weight="heavy">Tier 1</rich_text>
			<rich_text>

</rich_text>
			<rich_text weight="heavy">Protection</rich_text>
			<rich_text>: The cleric can protect himself from evil foes. He gains a +2 to all defences. This lasts for 1d4 +1 round per level of the cleric.

</rich_text>
			<rich_text weight="heavy">Bless</rich_text>
			<rich_text>: The cleric can pray a blessing on his companions. All allies within 30 feet recieve a +1 bonus to all attack rolls and to all defence scores. This bonus lasts for 1d4 +1 round per level of the cleric.

</rich_text>
			<rich_text underline="single" weight="heavy">Tier 2</rich_text>
			<rich_text>

</rich_text>
			<rich_text weight="heavy">Holy Smite</rich_text>
			<rich_text>: The cleric makes a Charisma attack against Willpower for all evil foes within 20 feet. If the attack succeeds the target takes 1d8 damage per 2 levels of the cleric. If the attack fails the enemy takes half damage. 

</rich_text>
			<rich_text weight="heavy">Turn Undead:</rich_text>
			<rich_text> A cleric can attempt to turn a number of hit dice of undead equal to twice his level. The undead targets must be in Close range. The cleric makes an attack with his Base Attack Bonus plus his Charisma against each target's Willpower Defense. If the attack succeeds then the target is turned.  A turned target must attempt to flee or at least move as far away from the cleric as possible for 1d6 rounds.  If the cleric has more than twice the hit dice of the undead, it is totally destroyed rather than being turned. 

</rich_text>
			<rich_text underline="single" weight="heavy">Tier 3</rich_text>
			<rich_text>

Holy Word: Any evil creature within 40 feet who hears the words suffers the following effect based on their hit dice:

HD equal to cleric:                 Deaf for 2d4 rounds.
HD greater than half the cleric's:  Stunned an unable to act for 2d4 rounds.
HD half or less than the cleric's:  Killed (or destroyed if undead)

There is no attack roll required for Holy Word.</rich_text>
		</node>
	</node>
	<node custom_icon_id="0" foreground="" is_bold="True" name="Combat Stunts" prog_lang="custom-colors" readonly="False" tags="" unique_id="76">
		<rich_text>Cleave: If your attack kills your foe, you can immediately make an additional attack against another foe within melee range.

Specialize: Gain a +1 to hit with your weapon of choice.

Weapon and Shield Style: 1 attack with Shield. Shield is a secondary weapon and no strength is applied to attack or damage.

Wounding Strike: +2 damage with weapon of choice.

Increased Proficiency: Either promote a weapon from Secondary to Primary or from Untrained to Secondary.

Massive Damage: When you make a modified roll of 25+ on an attack roll, your strike does double the number of dice in damage.  This does not double the dice from extra damage from a Thief's Sneak Attack or from Spells or Prayers.  This bonus applies to one weapon of your choice.

Subtle Blow: When attacking an opponent that is engaged with another foe, increase the size of your attack die by 1.  A d8 would become a d10.  A d10 would become a d12.  This has no affect on Sneak Attack dice.

Nerve Strike: Must be declared before the attack. If the attack hits, instead of damage the target is stunned and unable to act for 1 round.

Quick Strike: When using a Primary or Secondary melee weapon, the character may attack during the Movement and Missile phase of the round instead of the Melee and Magic phase.

Dual Wield: Character can fight with 2 weapons as long as the first weapon can be wielded in 1 hand and the second weapon is a small one-handed weapon.  The character gains 1 extra attack a round.  The additional attack is at their base attack bonus with no Strength added to the attack or damage.

Two Handed Style: Two handed weapons do an additional +2 damage. 

Armor Defense Style: When wearing medium or heavy armor and using a shield, get a +2 bonus to AC.</rich_text>
	</node>
	<node custom_icon_id="0" foreground="" is_bold="True" name="Skills" prog_lang="custom-colors" readonly="False" tags="" unique_id="58">
		<rich_text>Skills allow a character to get a bonus to an Ability Check where the skill applies. If the character is making an Intelligence Check and the Ancient History skill would be applicable to the check then she gets a +4 bonus if she has that skill.  She gets an additional +2 bonus for every slot after the first spent on a single skill.  

Some skills allow special actions and those are listed in the skill description. Some skills also make certain actions automatically successful.  
  
The GM may very well decide some actions cannot be attempted at all unless the character has that skill.  

Skill List:

