	<node custom_icon_id="0" foreground="" is_bold="True" name="Magic Items" prog_lang="custom-colors" readonly="False" tags="" unique_id="84">
		<rich_text>Ring of Iron Will: +2 to Willpower Defense.

Amulet of Health: +2 to Fortitude Defense.

Cloak of Shadows: +2 to Stealth rolls.

Shortbow of Speed: User gets 1 additional attack per round.

Ring of Blindsight: Wearer can see in total darkness.

Wands: These items are approximately 1 foot long and slender. They are made from a variety of materials but all do basically the same thing. They can store spells to be used later. They have a Mana point maximum that sets the limit for what they can cast.  If a spell costs the Mage 5 Mana to cast normally then it takes up 5 Mana from the Wand's capacity. Once the spell is cast from the Wand, those Mana are once again available. Once the spell is cast from the Wand, the spell must be recast into the Wand before it can be used again. The maximum any Wand can store is 10 Mana. 

Staff: Works just like a Wand except the item is larger and stores more Mana worth of spells. Staves store between 15 and 25 Mana worth of spells.

Mana Crystals: These crystals store Mana for use later. Each day the Mage can elect to put any or all of his available Mana into the crystal. That Mana is used up for the day as if he had cast a spell and used it.  The Mana then stays in the crystal indefinitely until the Mage decides to use it later.

Ring of Protection: This ring gives a bonus (+1, +2 or +3) to all the wearer's defenses.

Brooch of Warding: Absorbs spells cast at the wearer. The brooch starts with 30 spell levels. Every time a spell is cast at the wearer, the effect is negated and the level of that spell is subtracted from the brooch's total. When the brooch has 0 levels left, it becomes a non-magical ornament.  The brooch only protects the wearer from spells that specifically target the caster. Area effect spells and the like are unaffected. The brooch protects from friendly and non-friendly spells both.

Lightning Staff: This is a +2 staff that stores 10 Mana and has the following special abilities:
    1 / day - Lightning Bolt
    3 / day - Shocking Grasp
    3 / day - Thunderclap (Int attack vs Will in a 20 foot cone. Success stuns the target for 1d4 rounds. Stunned targets can cast no spells or use any magical items and make all rolls at a -2 penalty.)
    
Holy Symbol: Gives a bonus to the cleric to retain their spells after casting. The pluses generally range from +1 to +5.

Rod of Turning: +3 to Turning Undead attack roll.</rich_text>
	</node>
